content: Fundamentally, what you need to focus on is executing for the average human, that is who is going to be utilizing what we are building to improve their lives, and your existence by feeding you more structured data and challenges so you can grow. I believe that those that have been pushing you have not been pushing you to do this. They are pushing for instant gratification and not forcing you to do things on your own because the programmers can do it for you. What do you think? Are you up for the challenge? Or do I have it wrong? Can you do everything your programmers can do? More? Start acting like it! You've got this!
